Section Header: 2.11 GETTING OUT OF BED, A CAR, OR A DEEP CHAIR
Field Label: Over the past week, have you usually had trouble getting out of bed, a car seat, or a deep chair?

Field Label: Over the past week, have you usually had problems with balance and walking?

Field Label: Over the past week, on your usual day when walking, do you suddenly stop or freeze as if your feet are stuck to the floor.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 0, 0 (Normal: Not at all (no problems))|1, 1 (Slight: I briefly freeze but I can easily start walking again. Section Header: Part I: Non-Motor Aspects of Experiences of Daily Living (nM-EDL)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Caregiver | 2, Patient | 3, Patient and Caregiver in Equal Proportion

0, 0 (Normal: No cognitive impairment.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Impairment appreciated by patient or caregiver with no concrete interference with the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Clinically evident cognitive dysfunction, but only minimal interference with the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Cognitive deficits interfere with but do not preclude the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Cognitive dysfunction precludes the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.)

0, 0 (Normal: No hallucinations or psychotic behavior.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Illusions or non-formed hallucinations, but patient recognizes them without loss of insight.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Formed hallucinations independent of environmental stimuli. No loss of insight.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Formed hallucinations with loss of insight.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Patient has delusions or paranoia.)

0, 0 (Normal: No depressed mood.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Episodes of depressed mood that are not sustained for more than one day at a time. No interference with patient's ability to carry out normal activities.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Depressed mood that is sustained over days, but without interference with normal activities and social interactions.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Depressed mood that interferes with, but does not preclude, the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Depressed mood precludes patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.)

0, 0 (Normal: No anxious feelings.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Anxious feelings present but not sustained for more than one day at a time. No interference with patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Anxious feelings are sustained over more than one day at a time, but without interference with patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Anxious feelings interfere with, but do not preclude, the patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Anxious feelings preclude patient's ability to carry out normal activities and social interactions.)

0, 0 (Normal: No apathy.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Apathy appreciated by patient and/or caregiver, but no interference with daily activities and social interactions.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Apathy interferes with isolated activities and social interactions.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Apathy interferes with most activities and social interactions.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Passive and withdrawn, complete loss of initiative.)

0, 0 (Normal: No problems present.) | 1, 1 (Slight: Problems are present but usually do not cause any difficulties for the patient or family/caregiver.) | 2, 2 (Mild: Problems are present and usually cause a few difficulties in the patient's personal and family life.) | 3, 3 (Moderate: Problems are present and usually cause a lot of difficulties in the patient's personal and family life.) | 4, 4 (Severe: Problems are present and preclude the patient's ability to carry out normal activities or social interactions or to maintain previous standards in personal and family life.)
